  "response_text": "In black and white, a middle-aged man lies propped up in a bed at night, wearing striped button-front pajamas. A shaded bedside lamp glows on a small table to his left, casting soft light across the pillows, blanket, and dark metal headboard behind him. He looks uncomfortable and weary, his brow furrowed as he shifts under the covers. He gradually pushes himself more upright, clutching the blanket near his chest, and his face tightens as if fighting cold symptoms.\n\nAs he sits up, his mouth opens wide in an exaggerated sneeze or cough-like reaction. He recoils, then looks down miserably. The wider view reveals a large bed with rumpled pillows and blankets. Beside him, on the other side of the bed, a drawn, cartoon-like white figure appears among the pillows. It has a long pointed nose, a striped nightcap, button-like dots down its front, and thin outlined hands. Its flat, illustrated style contrasts with the live-action bedroom, making it look like a personified cold or symptom creature sharing the bed with him.\n\nThe man grabs a handkerchief or tissue and holds it to his nose. The cartoon cold figure leans toward him, its long nose and hands jutting forward. A jagged starburst shape flashes near the creature’s face, suggesting a sneeze or irritating burst aimed in his direction. The man turns away, still holding the tissue, his expression annoyed and sick. The cartoon figure remains upright beside him, looming from under the covers.\n\nThe man and the cartoon figure are shown closer together. The man, still in striped pajamas, looks sideways at the illustrated intruder with a tired, suspicious expression. The figure’s long nose and line-drawn features fill the space beside his shoulder. As the man slumps back against the pillow, the cartoon figure presses close, almost draped over him, reinforcing the sense that the cold is crowding him in bed.\n\nA product image then appears prominently in front of the bedroom scene, while the man and the cartoon figure blur behind it. The package shows a bottle on the front and the readable text “NEW,” “Vicks,” “NyQuil,” and “Nighttime Colds Medicine.” The box is held or positioned upright, square to the viewer, with the bottle graphic centered. The man remains in the background, still in bed, but the package becomes the clear visual focus.\n\nThe product is then handled at the bedside. A hand brings the NyQuil box closer, and the front label is readable again with “Vicks NyQuil” and “Nighttime Colds Medicine.” The box is opened, and the man’s hands remove or handle the bottle and cap. In a close view against the striped pajama fabric, he pours dark liquid from the NyQuil bottle into a small measuring cup. The liquid streams steadily from the bottle neck into the cup, emphasizing the medicine being prepared for use.\n\nThe man lifts the small cup to his lips and drinks. His face fills the image as he tips the cup back, eyes partly closed, swallowing the medicine. He lowers the cup, his mouth still pursed from the taste or the swallow, then relaxes slightly. The tight view of his face shows damp highlights and tired eyes, but his expression begins to soften.\n\nBack in the wider bedroom view, the NyQuil bottle or package now sits visibly on the bedside table near the lamp. The man, still propped up in bed, turns toward the cartoon cold figure beside him. He raises his hands and begins pushing the illustrated figure away. The figure flails with its long nose, pointed cap, and angular limbs, its flat paper-like body bending and tipping as the man shoves it across the blankets. He continues forcing it toward the far side of the bed. The cartoon creature collapses downward, sliding out of the man’s space, until it disappears below the blanket line. The man remains sitting up, looking more in control, with the covers settling back around him.\n\nHe then leans to one side and reaches toward the bedside area. His face shows a slight grimace that turns into a more satisfied, calmer look. The NyQuil package is brought forward again and held prominently in front of him. The background, with the man in striped pajamas and the bed behind him, becomes soft and indistinct, while the box is sharp and centered. The package again displays the large “NyQuil” name, “Vicks” above it, “NEW” in the upper corner, and “Nighttime Colds Medicine” beneath, with the bottle illustration on the front. The commercial ends with the product held steady as the dominant visual image, while the bedroom scene remains blurred behind it.",
